# Open WebUI connection to Azure OpenAI 

**(through my Helicone Installation):**

This is an Open AI type connection.

<img src="./assets/open-webui.png">

URL:  
This url points to my local helicone server (port 8785 is a nginx proxy server which injects a helicone header to send the traffic to Azure). The helicone api key is passed in through the URL. Note the [azure.com](http://azure.com)@ in front, (this is pure butchery) it essentially occupies a basic-auth position (which is ignored) but it ‘triggers’ Open WebUI into showing the extra Azure API Version field and using Azure paths.

The full URL is:  
*http://azure.com@192.168.100.86:8785/sk-helicone-k7gwrky-ue6usny-xqmc37i-uxraw7i*

Key:  
The Key is my Azure OpenAI assigned key.

API Version: and Model IDs:  
The API Version and Model ID go together and are assigned by Azure at the time a model is deployed.

Prefix ID:  
The prefix of Azure helps to keep models organized within the Open-WebUI interface.
